This is the miraculous
moment of resurrection

00:44:21.360 --> 00:44:24.190 align:middle line:84%
being portrayed in
the Maya tradition.

00:44:24.190 --> 00:44:28.590 align:middle line:10%
So here we see the turtle
shell, symbolizing Earth life.

00:44:28.590 --> 00:44:30.790 align:middle line:10%
And then squeezing
out of it, we're

00:44:30.790 --> 00:44:34.210 align:middle line:10%
going to see the first father
with his feathered headdress,

00:44:34.210 --> 00:44:38.050 align:middle line:10%
emerging from the earth plane
from the material realm,

00:44:38.050 --> 00:44:40.330 align:middle line:10%
entering into immaterial realm.

00:44:40.330 --> 00:44:43.730 align:middle line:84%
The cosmic turtle shell, says
Maya scholar David Gillette,

00:44:43.730 --> 00:44:46.630 align:middle line:84%
is the supernatural
maize kernel.

00:44:46.630 --> 00:44:49.560 align:middle line:84%
That's the divine spark,
the kernel of immortality

00:44:49.560 --> 00:44:54.180 align:middle line:84%
that burst open to allow the
resurrection body to soar up

00:44:54.180 --> 00:44:58.180 align:middle line:84%
from the realm of death into
the world of eternal life.

00:44:58.180 --> 00:45:01.740 align:middle line:10%
So this is the Maya
concept of resurrection,

00:45:01.740 --> 00:45:05.720 align:middle line:10%
of the emergence of the
divine spark within.

00:45:05.720 --> 00:45:07.610 align:middle line:10%
The First Father has
feathers sprouting

00:45:07.610 --> 00:45:09.430 align:middle line:10%
from his headdress
that symbolize

00:45:09.430 --> 00:45:13.170 align:middle line:10%
the leaves of the world
tree he is becoming.

00:45:13.170 --> 00:45:17.620 align:middle line:10%
Remember the acorn turning into
the oak, the world tree going

00:45:17.620 --> 00:45:20.800 align:middle line:10%
onward and upward, branching
out into other realms

00:45:20.800 --> 00:45:22.820 align:middle line:10%
and into other worlds.

00:45:22.820 --> 00:45:27.200 align:middle line:84%
So, a magnificent representation
of the successful soul,

00:45:27.200 --> 00:45:29.666 align:middle line:90%
the resurrected soul.

00:45:29.666 --> 00:45:31.040 align:middle line:84%
This takes us over
to Botticelli,

00:45:31.040 --> 00:45:34.300 align:middle line:84%
who will be the subject
of Clare's Beyond the Veil

00:45:34.300 --> 00:45:35.100 align:middle line:90%
segment.

00:45:35.100 --> 00:45:38.380 align:middle line:84%
What is Venus doing but
coming out of her shell

00:45:38.380 --> 00:45:40.290 align:middle line:90%
in a moment of resurrection?

00:45:40.290 --> 00:45:42.990 align:middle line:10%
We'll leave that
for her to unveil

00:45:42.990 --> 00:45:45.940 align:middle line:10%
all the other resurrection
symbolism in Botticelli's

00:45:45.940 --> 00:45:49.440 align:middle line:10%
magnificent masterpiece here.

00:45:49.440 --> 00:45:52.640 align:middle line:10%
Jesus, of course, went through
this experience in his baptism,

00:45:52.640 --> 00:45:56.700 align:middle line:10%
where he emerges from the
water, home of the sea shell,

00:45:56.700 --> 00:45:59.600 align:middle line:10%
and is then given, through
this cosmic vibration,

00:45:59.600 --> 00:46:01.990 align:middle line:10%
his new cloak, or
garment, of light.

00:46:01.990 --> 00:46:04.940 align:middle line:10%


00:46:04.940 --> 00:46:07.640 align:middle line:10%
In Buddhism, this
divine spark, this seed,

00:46:07.640 --> 00:46:11.480 align:middle line:10%
is called the "Adamantine
Nucleus of Radiant or Clear

00:46:11.480 --> 00:46:11.980 align:middle line:10%
Light."

00:46:11.980 --> 00:46:13.440 align:middle line:10%
That's a mouthful.

00:46:13.440 --> 00:46:15.700 align:middle line:10%
The term "Adamantine
Body" should

00:46:15.700 --> 00:46:19.680 align:middle line:10%
remind us of Adam, because it
refers to our primordial body

00:46:19.680 --> 00:46:21.750 align:middle line:10%
and also the Garden of Eden.

00:46:21.750 --> 00:46:23.960 align:middle line:10%
It refers to the
subtle body, also known

00:46:23.960 --> 00:46:27.750 align:middle line:10%
as the "vajra body" or
the "diamond body"--

00:46:27.750 --> 00:46:30.630 align:middle line:10%
very important concept,
also, to remember

00:46:30.630 --> 00:46:33.860 align:middle line:10%
when Clare gets into her
Beyond the Veil segment.

00:46:33.860 --> 00:46:36.290 align:middle line:10%
Growing or revealing
this body, according

00:46:36.290 --> 00:46:39.230 align:middle line:10%
to Buddhist alchemists,
is the great work.

00:46:39.230 --> 00:46:41.350 align:middle line:10%
It is arcanum.

00:46:41.350 --> 00:46:44.520 align:middle line:84%
And it's about awakening
the Adamantine body

00:46:44.520 --> 00:46:47.680 align:middle line:84%
and attaining the divine
body or the vajra body,

00:46:47.680 --> 00:46:51.810 align:middle line:84%
the body of light, expressed
in this beautiful illustration

00:46:51.810 --> 00:46:53.075 align:middle line:90%
here from Buddhism.

00:46:53.075 --> 00:46:56.300 align:middle line:90%


00:46:56.300 --> 00:46:58.950 align:middle line:10%
In closing for this
segment, I want

00:46:58.950 --> 00:47:01.970 align:middle line:10%
to share with you an
amazing revelation.

00:47:01.970 --> 00:47:04.400 align:middle line:84%
And that is that the
Greek word "adamas"

00:47:04.400 --> 00:47:08.050 align:middle line:84%
means unbreakable
and unalterable.

00:47:08.050 --> 00:47:10.630 align:middle line:84%
Our soul truly is
unbreakable no matter

00:47:10.630 --> 00:47:13.640 align:middle line:84%
what happens to us
on the Earth plane.

00:47:13.640 --> 00:47:18.170 align:middle line:84%
We are like that diamond,
unbreakable and unalterable.

00:47:18.170 --> 00:47:21.460 align:middle line:84%
And the Adamantine Land
is the Gnostic term

00:47:21.460 --> 00:47:24.230 align:middle line:84%
for the Heavenly realm
out of which we emerge.

00:47:24.230 --> 00:47:28.710 align:middle line:84%
We are truly divine and
eternal beings, unbreakable,

00:47:28.710 --> 00:47:30.012 align:middle line:90%
unalterable.

00:47:30.012 --> 00:47:31.970 align:middle line:84%
And what that means is
that this should give us

00:47:31.970 --> 00:47:35.750 align:middle line:84%
confidence to reach out
and to try new things,

00:47:35.750 --> 00:47:39.380 align:middle line:84%
knowing that we can't possibly
fail, in the eternal sense,

00:47:39.380 --> 00:47:42.505 align:middle line:84%
because it's all about awakening
our soul's true potential.

00:47:42.505 --> 00:47:45.760 align:middle line:90%


00:47:45.760 --> 00:47:49.530 align:middle line:10%
In esoteric Tibetan Buddhism,
Adamantine or Admantine Reality

00:47:49.530 --> 00:47:54.920 align:middle line:10%
connotes an unimaginably hard
substance that is impenetrable,

00:47:54.920 --> 00:47:56.820 align:middle line:10%
unbreakable, and
unyielding, as well as

00:47:56.820 --> 00:48:00.470 align:middle line:10%
being directly
linked to diamonds.

00:48:00.470 --> 00:48:03.861 align:middle line:10%
This takes us to a really
interesting transfiguration

00:48:03.861 --> 00:48:04.360 align:middle line:10%
image.

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:07.830 align:middle line:10%
I took this photo in the
chapel at Roslin Chapel

00:48:07.830 --> 00:48:10.270 align:middle line:10%
in Roslin, Scotland,
where we see

00:48:10.270 --> 00:48:14.250 align:middle line:10%
Jesus in this
transfiguration scene

00:48:14.250 --> 00:48:16.880 align:middle line:10%
with a diamond behind
him, indicating

00:48:16.880 --> 00:48:22.400 align:middle line:10%
that he has attained the diamond
body of the Buddhist tradition,

00:48:22.400 --> 00:48:25.880 align:middle line:10%
manifesting that light
body, that unalterable,

00:48:25.880 --> 00:48:29.410 align:middle line:10%
unbreakable light body.

00:48:29.410 --> 00:48:33.140 align:middle line:10%
Below the disciples is a Latin
inscription and a dedication

00:48:33.140 --> 00:48:36.810 align:middle line:10%
to James Francis Harry Sinclair,
the fifth Earl of Roslin.

00:48:36.810 --> 00:48:39.410 align:middle line:10%
The inscription
reads, "In Lumine tuo

00:48:39.410 --> 00:48:43.360 align:middle line:10%
bidebimus lumen," which has been
translated as "In your light

00:48:43.360 --> 00:48:45.870 align:middle line:10%
we shall see the divine light."

00:48:45.870 --> 00:48:48.810 align:middle line:84%
That's the Gnostic
call-- in your light.

00:48:48.810 --> 00:48:52.680 align:middle line:84%
In your light, we shall
see the divine light.

00:48:52.680 --> 00:48:56.040 align:middle line:84%
So let that diamond
within you glow.

00:48:56.040 --> 00:48:58.710 align:middle line:84%
Begin to radiate that
light with the confidence

00:48:58.710 --> 00:49:00.960 align:middle line:84%
that you are a divine
and unalterable,

00:49:00.960 --> 00:49:03.480 align:middle line:84%
unbreakable being
here on a mission

00:49:03.480 --> 00:49:06.670 align:middle line:90%
to spread divine light and love.

00:49:06.670 --> 00:49:10.560 align:middle line:10%
And in closing, I want to share
a meditation I learned about

00:49:10.560 --> 00:49:13.280 align:middle line:10%
from Jay Weidner in one
of his presentations,

00:49:13.280 --> 00:49:15.290 align:middle line:10%
where he quotes Dr.
Brian Weiss, who

00:49:15.290 --> 00:49:18.240 align:middle line:10%
says that during a
meditation or during a dream,

00:49:18.240 --> 00:49:22.490 align:middle line:10%
he saw a diamond in everybody's
chest, a beautiful diamond

00:49:22.490 --> 00:49:24.680 align:middle line:10%
with 1,000 facets.

00:49:24.680 --> 00:49:26.710 align:middle line:10%
Everybody's diamond
is the same, he said,

00:49:26.710 --> 00:49:31.030 align:middle line:10%
but some of the diamonds are
covered with dirt or tar.

00:49:31.030 --> 00:49:34.070 align:middle line:10%
And the job of the
soul seems to be

00:49:34.070 --> 00:49:37.600 align:middle line:10%
to clean the facets--
how beautiful.

00:49:37.600 --> 00:49:39.860 align:middle line:10%
When all of the
facets are clean,

00:49:39.860 --> 00:49:42.960 align:middle line:10%
the pressure seems to
dissolve, and the diamond

00:49:42.960 --> 00:49:48.080 align:middle line:10%
just radiates light, or
disperses into the universe.

00:49:48.080 --> 00:49:50.140 align:middle line:10%
Some people-- and
here's the key--

00:49:50.140 --> 00:49:52.894 align:middle line:10%
have polished a lot of
the facets, maybe 900

00:49:52.894 --> 00:49:56.740 align:middle line:10%
or 999, others only a few.

00:49:56.740 --> 00:49:59.470 align:middle line:10%
They have a lot of work
to do, says Dr. Weiss.

00:49:59.470 --> 00:50:01.280 align:middle line:10%
Then he understood.

00:50:01.280 --> 00:50:05.030 align:middle line:10%
Everybody's diamond is the same.

00:50:05.030 --> 00:50:08.980 align:middle line:10%
1,000 facets and the
potential is exactly the same,

00:50:08.980 --> 00:50:12.120 align:middle line:10%
and everybody is on
the same journey.

00:50:12.120 --> 00:50:15.070 align:middle line:10%
So let that light
shine within you.

00:50:15.070 --> 00:50:18.020 align:middle line:84%
Clean the facets
of your diamond,

00:50:18.020 --> 00:50:20.150 align:middle line:84%
and let that light
shine through.

00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:22.160 align:middle line:84%
And as you allow
your light to shine,

00:50:22.160 --> 00:50:26.110 align:middle line:84%
it allows my light to
shine greater, too.

00:50:26.110 --> 00:50:29.228 align:middle line:90%
That's "Arcanum."

00:50:29.228 --> 00:50:32.090 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:50:32.090 --> 00:50:34.960 align:middle line:10%


00:50:34.960 --> 00:50:37.110 align:middle line:10%
And now, in this segment
of Beyond the Veil,

00:50:37.110 --> 00:50:40.000 align:middle line:10%
Clare is going to take us closer
to the mysteries of the divine

00:50:40.000 --> 00:50:43.340 align:middle line:10%
spark through the eyes of
the great Renaissance master

00:50:43.340 --> 00:50:45.370 align:middle line:10%
Sandro Botticelli.

00:50:45.370 --> 00:50:48.530 align:middle line:10%
>>CLARE: In this segment
of Beyond the Veil,

00:50:48.530 --> 00:50:52.610 align:middle line:10%
we are going to explore the
work of Sandro Botticelli,

00:50:52.610 --> 00:50:56.960 align:middle line:10%
one of the definitive painters
of the Italian Renaissance,

00:50:56.960 --> 00:50:59.990 align:middle line:10%
and a man who was not
only privy to arcanum,

00:50:59.990 --> 00:51:02.440 align:middle line:10%
but he also painted it.

00:51:02.440 --> 00:51:11.200 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:51:11.200 --> 00:51:15.120 align:middle line:10%
Born to a poor tanner in the
back streets of Florence,

00:51:15.120 --> 00:51:17.920 align:middle line:10%
Alessandro Filipepi
was brought up

00:51:17.920 --> 00:51:20.550 align:middle line:10%
by his brother, who
gave him the nickname

00:51:20.550 --> 00:51:25.410 align:middle line:10%
Botticelli, meaning
little barrel.

00:51:25.410 --> 00:51:28.050 align:middle line:10%
The name stuck, and
Botticelli's art

00:51:28.050 --> 00:51:31.910 align:middle line:10%
became the most intelligent,
creative, and recognizable

00:51:31.910 --> 00:51:36.000 align:middle line:10%
voices of the
Florentine Renaissance

00:51:36.000 --> 00:51:39.760 align:middle line:10%
that also saw the rise
of Donatello, Leonardo,

00:51:39.760 --> 00:51:45.780 align:middle line:10%
Michelangelo, and Raphael,
amongst other great masters.

00:51:45.780 --> 00:51:49.010 align:middle line:10%
This painting is part of
an altarpiece commissioned

00:51:49.010 --> 00:51:53.220 align:middle line:10%
for a convent for
repentant prostitutes.

00:51:53.220 --> 00:51:56.910 align:middle line:10%
In the center is a vision
of the Trinity, God

00:51:56.910 --> 00:52:00.900 align:middle line:10%
the father, a dove,
symbolizing the Holy Spirit,

00:52:00.900 --> 00:52:03.790 align:middle line:10%
and Christ on the cross.

00:52:03.790 --> 00:52:06.610 align:middle line:84%
Flanking this
surprising apparition

00:52:06.610 --> 00:52:10.370 align:middle line:84%
are John the Baptist,
patron Saint of Florence,

00:52:10.370 --> 00:52:16.340 align:middle line:84%
and Mary Magdalene,
patroness of the convent.

00:52:16.340 --> 00:52:21.220 align:middle line:10%
By the late 1460s, Botticelli
had made a name for himself

00:52:21.220 --> 00:52:24.920 align:middle line:10%
under the apprenticeship
of the great Filippo Lippi,

00:52:24.920 --> 00:52:28.550 align:middle line:10%
where he was spotted by agents
of the most powerful family

00:52:28.550 --> 00:52:33.340 align:middle line:10%
of the Renaissance, the
Medicis, who were also

00:52:33.340 --> 00:52:38.020 align:middle line:10%
among history's
greatest mystic seekers.

00:52:38.020 --> 00:52:42.760 align:middle line:10%
The Medicis were immensely
wealthy and powerful.

00:52:42.760 --> 00:52:45.880 align:middle line:10%
They were obsessed with arcanum.

00:52:45.880 --> 00:52:49.290 align:middle line:84%
They hoped to create
a new Golden Age.

00:52:49.290 --> 00:52:54.590 align:middle line:84%
Botticelli would help
them visualize it.

00:52:54.590 --> 00:52:58.960 align:middle line:84%
The Medicis considered
themselves modern-day Magi.

00:52:58.960 --> 00:53:02.860 align:middle line:84%
The Chapel of the Magi
occupies an important place

00:53:02.860 --> 00:53:05.100 align:middle line:90%
in the Medici palace.

00:53:05.100 --> 00:53:08.970 align:middle line:10%
The chapel is famous for
this series of wall paintings

00:53:08.970 --> 00:53:12.360 align:middle line:10%
by Benozzo Gozzoli,
with the angels

00:53:12.360 --> 00:53:15.500 align:middle line:10%
in adoration in the
rectangular apse

00:53:15.500 --> 00:53:20.200 align:middle line:10%
and the journey of the
Magi in the large hall.

00:53:20.200 --> 00:53:25.150 align:middle line:10%
On the north wall, in the
entourage of the Magi Caspar,

00:53:25.150 --> 00:53:27.780 align:middle line:10%
is an ideal portrait
of Lorenzo de'

00:53:27.780 --> 00:53:30.090 align:middle line:10%
Medici, the future magnifico.

00:53:30.090 --> 00:53:32.630 align:middle line:90%


00:53:32.630 --> 00:53:37.720 align:middle line:84%
The meaning of Medici in
Italian is medical doctor,

00:53:37.720 --> 00:53:41.420 align:middle line:84%
although some believe
it means magic.

00:53:41.420 --> 00:53:48.170 align:middle line:84%
In 1460, 14 books called
Corpus Hermeticum were covertly

00:53:48.170 --> 00:53:51.440 align:middle line:84%
bought by a monk who
miraculously escaped

00:53:51.440 --> 00:53:57.080 align:middle line:84%
the Byzantium siege in 1453
to the court of Cosimo de'

00:53:57.080 --> 00:54:00.530 align:middle line:90%
Medici, ruler of Florence.

00:54:00.530 --> 00:54:03.430 align:middle line:84%
The central texts of
the Corpus Hermeticum

00:54:03.430 --> 00:54:06.065 align:middle line:84%
were lost to the West
in classical times.

00:54:06.065 --> 00:54:08.870 align:middle line:90%


00:54:08.870 --> 00:54:11.640 align:middle line:84%
The Corpus Hermeticum
texts dwell

00:54:11.640 --> 00:54:15.950 align:middle line:84%
upon the oneness
and goodness of God,

00:54:15.950 --> 00:54:21.640 align:middle line:84%
urge purification of the soul,
and defend religious practices

00:54:21.640 --> 00:54:26.500 align:middle line:84%
such as the
veneration of images.

00:54:26.500 --> 00:54:29.695 align:middle line:84%
The image itself will
show you the way,

00:54:29.695 --> 00:54:30.820 align:middle line:90%
says the Corpus Hermeticum.

00:54:30.820 --> 00:54:34.400 align:middle line:90%


00:54:34.400 --> 00:54:36.410 align:middle line:10%
Written by unknown
authors in Egypt

00:54:36.410 --> 00:54:40.360 align:middle line:10%
sometime before the end
of the 3rd century CE,

00:54:40.360 --> 00:54:42.780 align:middle line:10%
the Corpus Hermeticum
were part of

00:54:42.780 --> 00:54:45.840 align:middle line:10%
a once-substantial
literature attributed

00:54:45.840 --> 00:54:50.010 align:middle line:10%
to the mythic figure
of Hermes Trismegistus,

00:54:50.010 --> 00:54:54.300 align:middle line:10%
a Hellenistic fusion
of the Greek god Hermes

00:54:54.300 --> 00:54:58.280 align:middle line:10%
and the Egyptian god Thoth.

00:54:58.280 --> 00:55:03.710 align:middle line:10%
Corpus Hermeticum was
translated by Marsilio Ficino.

00:55:03.710 --> 00:55:06.750 align:middle line:84%
In order to get
arcanum, we must get

00:55:06.750 --> 00:55:10.270 align:middle line:90%
to know this Renaissance Magi.

00:55:10.270 --> 00:55:16.950 align:middle line:10%
High priest, physician,
musician, magician, astrologer,

00:55:16.950 --> 00:55:22.260 align:middle line:10%
and Christian, he was the
original Renaissance man.

00:55:22.260 --> 00:55:28.550 align:middle line:84%
He is featured in Ghirlandaio's
"An Angel Visits Zechariah."

00:55:28.550 --> 00:55:32.840 align:middle line:10%
He also appears in a scene
showing Plato and Ficnino

00:55:32.840 --> 00:55:36.610 align:middle line:10%
with Hermes in Sienna Cathedral.

00:55:36.610 --> 00:55:42.160 align:middle line:10%
Ficino and his successors
regarded Hermes Trismegistus

00:55:42.160 --> 00:55:44.910 align:middle line:10%
as a contemporary of Moses.

00:55:44.910 --> 00:55:49.240 align:middle line:10%
And his teachings were seen as a
perennial philosophy, predating

00:55:49.240 --> 00:55:52.990 align:middle line:10%
yet anticipating
Christianity with its roots

00:55:52.990 --> 00:55:55.960 align:middle line:10%
in ancient Egypt.

00:55:55.960 --> 00:56:02.040 align:middle line:84%
For him, Jesus was the exemplar
of ultimate human potential.

00:56:02.040 --> 00:56:07.090 align:middle line:84%
He sought to fuse
Christianity with its roots.

00:56:07.090 --> 00:56:09.370 align:middle line:10%
Bellini's "Blood
of the Redeemer"

00:56:09.370 --> 00:56:12.080 align:middle line:10%
shows Jesus in the foreground.

00:56:12.080 --> 00:56:16.830 align:middle line:10%
In the background, the
caduceus wand of arcanum

00:56:16.830 --> 00:56:20.615 align:middle line:10%
is passed off,
suggesting the torch had

00:56:20.615 --> 00:56:22.143 align:middle line:10%
been passed to Christianity.

00:56:22.143 --> 00:56:24.960 align:middle line:90%


00:56:24.960 --> 00:56:27.330 align:middle line:84%
Ficino realized
that Christianity

00:56:27.330 --> 00:56:30.410 align:middle line:84%
was a variation,
an interpretation

00:56:30.410 --> 00:56:33.300 align:middle line:84%
of a group of followers
of the Corpus Hermeticum,

00:56:33.300 --> 00:56:35.750 align:middle line:84%
specifically the
cult of Serapis.

00:56:35.750 --> 00:56:38.290 align:middle line:90%


00:56:38.290 --> 00:56:43.980 align:middle line:84%
Ficino also revived Platonism,
the philosophy of Plato.

00:56:43.980 --> 00:56:47.960 align:middle line:84%
The human soul originated
in the higher world

00:56:47.960 --> 00:56:51.490 align:middle line:84%
but is trapped in the
body, in the lower world.

00:56:51.490 --> 00:56:54.330 align:middle line:84%
And Plato's writing
sometimes described

00:56:54.330 --> 00:56:57.100 align:middle line:84%
the return, or
ascent, of the soul

00:56:57.100 --> 00:57:02.500 align:middle line:84%
to its true, perfect home, the
unity of the one that is God.

00:57:02.500 --> 00:57:05.310 align:middle line:90%


00:57:05.310 --> 00:57:09.790 align:middle line:10%
Ficino wrote and performed music
that drew down or attracted

00:57:09.790 --> 00:57:14.130 align:middle line:10%
stellar influences, the
music of the spheres.

00:57:14.130 --> 00:57:16.970 align:middle line:10%
This was possible
because the human soul

00:57:16.970 --> 00:57:20.300 align:middle line:10%
is made of star
stuff, he taught.

00:57:20.300 --> 00:57:23.330 align:middle line:10%
Ficino wrote extensively
about techniques

00:57:23.330 --> 00:57:26.620 align:middle line:10%
whereby planetary powers
were to be invoked

00:57:26.620 --> 00:57:30.600 align:middle line:10%
by the principles
of Hermetic analogy.

00:57:30.600 --> 00:57:33.450 align:middle line:10%
As above, so below.

00:57:33.450 --> 00:57:36.150 align:middle line:10%
As within, so without.

00:57:36.150 --> 00:57:38.940 align:middle line:10%
This is the Hermetic
law of Ficino.

00:57:38.940 --> 00:57:41.720 align:middle line:10%


00:57:41.720 --> 00:57:45.660 align:middle line:10%
Ficino believed he could draw
down the power of the stars

00:57:45.660 --> 00:57:49.860 align:middle line:10%
and planets to aid in
his spiritual evolution.

00:57:49.860 --> 00:57:53.190 align:middle line:84%
We are trapped on
Earth, he believed.

00:57:53.190 --> 00:57:58.780 align:middle line:84%
The only way out was to
refine the soul and descend

00:57:58.780 --> 00:58:01.570 align:middle line:90%
to the Heavenly realms.

00:58:01.570 --> 00:58:04.240 align:middle line:84%
Ficino wrote extensively
about techniques

00:58:04.240 --> 00:58:07.670 align:middle line:84%
whereby planetary powers
were to be invoked

00:58:07.670 --> 00:58:10.840 align:middle line:84%
by principles of
Hermetic analogy.

00:58:10.840 --> 00:58:13.970 align:middle line:84%
Chiefly accused of
being his follower,

00:58:13.970 --> 00:58:16.580 align:middle line:84%
and the man who
incorporated this knowledge

00:58:16.580 --> 00:58:21.260 align:middle line:84%
in his paintings, was
Sandro Botticelli.

00:58:21.260 --> 00:58:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Botticelli would help
the Medicis visualize

00:58:24.330 --> 00:58:27.960 align:middle line:84%
the new Golden Age,
and in so doing,

00:58:27.960 --> 00:58:33.610 align:middle line:84%
is credited with creating
a whole new genre of art.

00:58:33.610 --> 00:58:36.300 align:middle line:10%
Embedded symbolism
and private jokes

00:58:36.300 --> 00:58:40.220 align:middle line:10%
characterize this new
genre; so did the intention

00:58:40.220 --> 00:58:46.030 align:middle line:10%
to draw down planetary
powers into his art.

00:58:46.030 --> 00:58:50.320 align:middle line:10%
Renaissance art, including
Raphael, but particularly

00:58:50.320 --> 00:58:53.430 align:middle line:10%
that of Botticelli,
can only be understood

00:58:53.430 --> 00:58:59.290 align:middle line:10%
with this magical knowledge,
or arcanum, in mind.

00:58:59.290 --> 00:59:02.560 align:middle line:84%
Known also as "The
Madonna of the Book,"

00:59:02.560 --> 00:59:05.870 align:middle line:84%
this painting represents
the Virgin and child

00:59:05.870 --> 00:59:08.000 align:middle line:90%
in a domestic setting.

00:59:08.000 --> 00:59:12.930 align:middle line:84%
Intent on reading a volume,
perhaps the Book of Love,

00:59:12.930 --> 00:59:17.980 align:middle line:84%
Jesus holds a golden crown
and three shafts of light.

00:59:17.980 --> 00:59:20.936 align:middle line:84%
These could represent the
triple shafts of enlightenment.

00:59:20.936 --> 00:59:24.530 align:middle line:90%


00:59:24.530 --> 00:59:29.060 align:middle line:10%
"The Magnificat" fused
Botticelli's Christian beliefs

00:59:29.060 --> 00:59:32.540 align:middle line:10%
with Renaissance
naturalistic style.

00:59:32.540 --> 00:59:36.450 align:middle line:84%
The Virgin Mary wears
her cloak of many colors.

00:59:36.450 --> 00:59:42.010 align:middle line:84%
Two angels place a
plasma-like crown on her head.

00:59:42.010 --> 00:59:44.950 align:middle line:84%
The title of the painting
derives from the word

00:59:44.950 --> 00:59:48.680 align:middle line:84%
"magnificat," which is written
in the book held by the two

00:59:48.680 --> 00:59:50.540 align:middle line:90%
angels.

00:59:50.540 --> 00:59:56.710 align:middle line:84%
Mary is completing the last
words of the prayer as her son

00:59:56.710 --> 00:59:59.890 align:middle line:90%
guides her hand.

00:59:59.890 --> 01:00:04.760 align:middle line:10%
Botticelli befriended the heirs
to the Medici empire, Lorenzo

01:00:04.760 --> 01:00:07.960 align:middle line:10%
and his brother Guiliano.

01:00:07.960 --> 01:00:11.490 align:middle line:10%
Lorenzo's court, and
indeed all of Florence,

01:00:11.490 --> 01:00:16.410 align:middle line:10%
was crowded with secret
groups and shadowy societies.

01:00:16.410 --> 01:00:20.270 align:middle line:84%
Florentine coppersmith
Bartelomeo Masi

01:00:20.270 --> 01:00:24.760 align:middle line:84%
recorded in his
diary in April 1492

01:00:24.760 --> 01:00:28.070 align:middle line:84%
that as Lorenzo de'
Medici lay dying,

01:00:28.070 --> 01:00:31.280 align:middle line:84%
a violent storm damaged
the duomo's bell

01:00:31.280 --> 01:00:36.560 align:middle line:84%
tower and buildings in the
Palazzo Medici neighborhood.

01:00:36.560 --> 01:00:40.610 align:middle line:84%
The storm was caused by
the release of a demon

01:00:40.610 --> 01:00:44.395 align:middle line:84%
that Lorenzo had kept imprisoned
in a ring for many years.

01:00:44.395 --> 01:00:46.940 align:middle line:90%


01:00:46.940 --> 01:00:51.740 align:middle line:10%
An unusually bright star loomed
over the villa at Careggi,

01:00:51.740 --> 01:00:57.230 align:middle line:10%
fell, and disappeared at the
moment of Lorenzo's death.

01:00:57.230 --> 01:01:01.000 align:middle line:10%
Lorenzo has been called
"an heir to King Solomon"

01:01:01.000 --> 01:01:04.880 align:middle line:10%
for his ability to
magically bind demons

01:01:04.880 --> 01:01:10.780 align:middle line:10%
and draw planetary influences
into engraved stones.

01:01:10.780 --> 01:01:13.810 align:middle line:10%
It is claimed that he
sought these powers

01:01:13.810 --> 01:01:15.630 align:middle line:10%
to assure his souls' ascension.

01:01:15.630 --> 01:01:18.170 align:middle line:10%


01:01:18.170 --> 01:01:22.890 align:middle line:10%
Botticelli's "La Primavera"
was neither portrait, icon,

01:01:22.890 --> 01:01:25.110 align:middle line:10%
nor holy celebration.

01:01:25.110 --> 01:01:29.230 align:middle line:10%
It was pure fantasy,
inspired by poetry

01:01:29.230 --> 01:01:33.460 align:middle line:10%
and felled by a
vivid imagination.

01:01:33.460 --> 01:01:36.030 align:middle line:10%
This much-analyzed
painting shows

01:01:36.030 --> 01:01:40.220 align:middle line:10%
Venus, ancient goddess
of beauty and fertility,

01:01:40.220 --> 01:01:45.650 align:middle line:10%
celebrating the arrival
of spring, la primavera.

01:01:45.650 --> 01:01:50.060 align:middle line:10%
She is surrounded by
allegorical figures representing

01:01:50.060 --> 01:01:53.495 align:middle line:10%
the virtues and gods
of the ancient world.

01:01:53.495 --> 01:01:56.060 align:middle line:10%


01:01:56.060 --> 01:02:01.230 align:middle line:10%
"The Birth of Venus" was unlike
any other painting of its time.

01:02:01.230 --> 01:02:06.850 align:middle line:10%
Botticelli presents us with
a beautiful world to enter.

01:02:06.850 --> 01:02:09.450 align:middle line:84%
Featuring the
goddess of love, it

01:02:09.450 --> 01:02:12.530 align:middle line:84%
was designed to be hung
above the marital bed.

01:02:12.530 --> 01:02:17.450 align:middle line:84%
It was a daring celebration
of human desire.

01:02:17.450 --> 01:02:21.450 align:middle line:84%
Previous to this, it was
unheard of to see a woman,

01:02:21.450 --> 01:02:24.760 align:middle line:90%
save for Eve, in the nude.

01:02:24.760 --> 01:02:27.020 align:middle line:84%
The painting was
so controversial it

01:02:27.020 --> 01:02:31.600 align:middle line:84%
was kept behind closed
doors for half a century.

01:02:31.600 --> 01:02:35.230 align:middle line:84%
It is considered one of
the most iconic pieces

01:02:35.230 --> 01:02:39.730 align:middle line:90%
in the history of Western art.

01:02:39.730 --> 01:02:43.160 align:middle line:84%
Metallic gold is
everywhere in the painting.

01:02:43.160 --> 01:02:47.950 align:middle line:84%
It's in zephyr's wings
and in the tree leaves.

01:02:47.950 --> 01:02:51.710 align:middle line:84%
The entwined zephyr push
the winds to the goddess.

01:02:51.710 --> 01:02:54.620 align:middle line:90%


01:02:54.620 --> 01:02:59.060 align:middle line:84%
Our eye is drawn to Venus
coming out of her shell.

01:02:59.060 --> 01:03:01.970 align:middle line:84%
According to many
analysts, Botticelli

01:03:01.970 --> 01:03:07.500 align:middle line:84%
is depicting the spiritual
beauty of the soul.

01:03:07.500 --> 01:03:10.710 align:middle line:84%
Botticelli paints
Venus being born

01:03:10.710 --> 01:03:13.310 align:middle line:90%
from the philosophical sea.

01:03:13.310 --> 01:03:17.700 align:middle line:84%
This represents
the divine spark.

01:03:17.700 --> 01:03:21.290 align:middle line:84%
It has the same meaning
as the Mayan resurrection

01:03:21.290 --> 01:03:26.470 align:middle line:84%
scene of the First Father
emerging from the turtle shell

01:03:26.470 --> 01:03:29.050 align:middle line:90%
or Earth life.

01:03:29.050 --> 01:03:31.870 align:middle line:84%
Like Botticelli's
other masterpiece,

01:03:31.870 --> 01:03:35.740 align:middle line:84%
"Pallas and the Centaur,"
"The Birth of Venus"

01:03:35.740 --> 01:03:40.660 align:middle line:84%
is painted on canvas,
fairly unusual for its time,

01:03:40.660 --> 01:03:42.570 align:middle line:84%
using a technique
of thin tempura,

01:03:42.570 --> 01:03:48.060 align:middle line:84%
based on the use of diluted
egg yolk, which lends itself

01:03:48.060 --> 01:03:51.260 align:middle line:84%
particularly well to give
the painting that aspect

01:03:51.260 --> 01:03:52.750 align:middle line:90%
of extraordinary transparency.

01:03:52.750 --> 01:03:55.470 align:middle line:90%


01:03:55.470 --> 01:04:01.000 align:middle line:84%
Why is Venus being
mantled with red?

01:04:01.000 --> 01:04:05.730 align:middle line:84%
An answer is found in alchemy,
where a white phase, called

01:04:05.730 --> 01:04:10.560 align:middle line:84%
Venus, precedes
going to redness.

01:04:10.560 --> 01:04:17.900 align:middle line:84%
Here we recall that
Wisdom's mantle is red.

01:04:17.900 --> 01:04:22.250 align:middle line:84%
Is Venus being
cloaked in wisdom?

01:04:22.250 --> 01:04:26.540 align:middle line:84%
In 1482, the Medici
family commissioned

01:04:26.540 --> 01:04:31.440 align:middle line:84%
Sandro Botticelli's painting
of "Pallas and the Centaur."

01:04:31.440 --> 01:04:36.690 align:middle line:90%
This is Athena in all her glory.

01:04:36.690 --> 01:04:39.990 align:middle line:84%
The painting, cited as
"Camilla and a Satyr"

01:04:39.990 --> 01:04:42.862 align:middle line:84%
is recorded in the interior
of the so-called Old

01:04:42.862 --> 01:04:47.220 align:middle line:84%
House of the family in a
room on the ground floor,

01:04:47.220 --> 01:04:52.130 align:middle line:84%
alongside the chamber of
Lorenzo de Pierre Francisco,

01:04:52.130 --> 01:04:56.260 align:middle line:84%
together with the "Primavera,"
also by Botticelli.

01:04:56.260 --> 01:04:59.670 align:middle line:84%
It was hung high above the door
leading to the antechamber.

01:04:59.670 --> 01:05:02.420 align:middle line:90%


01:05:02.420 --> 01:05:07.560 align:middle line:10%
Athena is wearing a light
gown, white and transparent,

01:05:07.560 --> 01:05:11.150 align:middle line:10%
decorated with
diamond-tipped tipped rings.

01:05:11.150 --> 01:05:14.510 align:middle line:10%
She is wrapped in a
large green cloak.

01:05:14.510 --> 01:05:19.390 align:middle line:10%
A mesh of olive shoots encircles
her shoulders, arms, breast,

01:05:19.390 --> 01:05:24.070 align:middle line:10%
and thighs, forming a sort of
vegetable breast plate, which

01:05:24.070 --> 01:05:27.650 align:middle line:10%
makes her gown
cling to the body.

01:05:27.650 --> 01:05:30.970 align:middle line:10%
Botticelli decorated
the goddess' delicious

01:05:30.970 --> 01:05:36.090 align:middle line:10%
dress with a diamond ring
and the three-ring symbol

01:05:36.090 --> 01:05:41.240 align:middle line:10%
of the Medici, which is also
the symbol of the Cintamani,

01:05:41.240 --> 01:05:45.210 align:middle line:10%
or wish-fulfilling jewel.

01:05:45.210 --> 01:05:47.800 align:middle line:10%
The points where
the branches cross

01:05:47.800 --> 01:05:52.120 align:middle line:10%
are fixed with diamond-tipped
rings, while on her nipples

01:05:52.120 --> 01:05:54.900 align:middle line:10%
are two mounted diamonds.

01:05:54.900 --> 01:06:00.610 align:middle line:10%
This indicates she is in
her light, or diamond, body.

01:06:00.610 --> 01:06:03.550 align:middle line:10%
Her long, thick,
blonde tresses are

01:06:03.550 --> 01:06:07.490 align:middle line:10%
adorned with a wreath of
entwined olive branches

01:06:07.490 --> 01:06:10.180 align:middle line:10%
with a diamond at the top
within a four-leaf setting.

01:06:10.180 --> 01:06:14.874 align:middle line:90%


